  "prompt": "How do you know who viewed you video on Instagram?",
  "response": "Instagram doesn't typically provide a detailed list of every individual who has viewed your video. How much information you get depends on the type of content you're posting:\n\n*   **Instagram Stories:**\n    *   You can see a list of everyone who viewed your story within 24 hours of posting it. Tap on your story, and then swipe up from the bottom of the screen to see the viewers.\n\n*   **Instagram Reels:**\n    *   You can see the total number of views, but you can't see a list of individual viewers.\n\n*   **Instagram Video Posts (on your feed):**\n    *   Similar to Reels, you can see the total number of views, but not a list of individual viewers.\n\n*   **Instagram Live:**\n    *   While the Live video is active, you can see the number of viewers and who is watching live. However, after the Live ends, you can only see the total number of views if you choose to share the replay. You won't see a list of individual viewers who watched the replay.\n\n**In Summary:**\n\n*   **You can see a list of viewers for Instagram Stories.**\n*   **For Reels, regular video posts, and Live replays, you only see the total number of views, not a list of individuals.**\n\n**Why doesn't Instagram show a list of all viewers?**\n\nLikely for privacy reasons. Not everyone wants their viewing activity to be public knowledge.",
